  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nI'm working with a private repo branched from v2022.08.03 but I can see that the issue is present in the latest 'devel'. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nA bad transaction should be removed from the head of the list in the  filterBadTransactions() function. For example:\r\n```\r\n\t\t// Make sure the sender is an EOA (EIP-3607)\r\n\t\tif !account.IsEmptyCodeHash() {\r\n\t\t\ttransactions = transactions[1:]\r\n\t\t\tcontinue\r\n\t\t}\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nSome of the conditions typo \"1:\" to \":1\". The first element is left in place to fail again on the next loop iteration.\r\n\r\n```\r\n\t\tsender, ok := transaction.GetSender()\r\n\t\tif !ok {\r\n\t\t\ttransactions = transactions[:1]\r\n\t\t\tcontinue\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t\tvar account accounts.Account\r\n\t\tok, err := rawdb.ReadAccount(simulationTx, sender, &account)\r\n\t\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\t\treturn nil, err\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t\tif !ok {\r\n\t\t\ttransactions = transactions[:1]\r\n\t\t\tcontinue\r\n\t\t}\r\n```\r\n",
